9 An Act relating to schools; prohibiting private
schools from requiring a parent or guardian to
10 participate in the Oklahoma Parental Choice Tax
Credit Program; and providing for codification.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 28-104 of Title 70, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 Private schools accredited by the State Board of Education or
18 another accrediting association shall not, as a condition of
19 acceptance, enrollment, or application, require that a student's
20 parent or guardian participate in the Oklahoma Parental Choice Tax
21 Credit Program created in Section 28-101 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma
22 Statutes.
